OL,6,FBut for the last decade she has been
OL,7,Flocked up in a because she has a
OL,8,Flearning disability.
OL,10,FShe was sectioned under the Mental
OL,11,FHealth Act and although she has been
OL,12,Fwell enough to live in the community
OL,13,Ffor the past two years, she can't
OL,14,Fbecause there is nowhere for her to go.
OL,16,FDue to the lack of funds, there is no
OL,17,Fadequate community provision for her
OL,18,Fto live the independent life she longs
OL,19,Ffor, so she has no choice but to stay
OL,20,Flocked away.
